---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Subtle Somatics" description="Connecting you to your innate resources through somatic coaching and energetic modalities for deeper self-awareness and growth." lang="en" altLangUrl="/de/ueber-mich">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner">
      <h1>Empower Your Presence</h1>
      <p>Connecting you to your innate resources through somatic coaching and energetic modalities for deeper self-awareness and growth.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About Kaja -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="content-split">
      <div class="content-text">
        <h2>Hi, I'm Kaja.</h2>
        <p>I believe that within each person lies a vast reservoir of innate resources — strength, love, radiance, trust, and peace. These qualities are not something to be acquired from outside, but something to be uncovered, remembered, and embodied from within.</p>
        <p>What I've come to deeply appreciate about myself is my sincere, deep care and skilled attunement that facilitates nourishment, healing and unfolding. I see and mirror qualities of resourcefulness in others — and I feel deeply honoured and blessed to offer Spinal Energetics and presence-based coaching.</p>
        <p>My approach draws on the wisdom of the body-mind-soul system, working with the natural intelligence that already knows how to heal, integrate, and align. Through gentle presence and deep listening, we create the conditions for what is most alive and true in you to emerge.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-image">
        <img src="/images/kaja-profile.jpg" alt="Kaja Possert-Bienzle" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Journey -->
  <section class="section section-cream">
    <div class="journey-content text-center">
      <h2>An Unfolding Journey</h2>
      <p>I've committed a lot of my focus to my inner unfolding over the past years — so I can increasingly embody my purpose in this life.</p>
      <p>This path led me to integral we-space practice — being present to what wants to happen through us in a group, like an interpersonal meditation. I searched for an aligned, leading-edge coaching approach and unfolded deeply through Aletheia coaching, encompassing parts, process and depth work.</p>
      <p>I co-facilitated leadership trainings, worked in sociopsychiatric settings, and embarked on education towards licensed psychotherapy. Along the way, I experienced plant medicine journeys, extensive meditation, and a yoga training — and put much attention on integrating my development.</p>
      <p>Then I discovered Spinal Energetics — a unique somatic-energetic modality working with the body's natural movement while incorporating sound, energy, and movement. I noticed the intricate and beautiful subtle movements within my body that naturally support emotional processing, getting in touch with deep underlying strength, and a knowing of peace.</p>
      <p>Today, I accompany individuals and groups in unfolding what is alive and true — through subtle coaching, somatic work, and collective practices.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Values -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="values-grid">
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Presence</h3>
        <p>Being fully here — with what is. Not fixing, not striving, but meeting the moment with open awareness.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Wholeness</h3>
        <p>Recognising that you are already whole. Our work is about removing the layers that obscure this truth.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Embodiment</h3>
        <p>Living from the body's wisdom, not just the mind's understanding. True knowing happens in the tissues, the breath, the bones.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Trust</h3>
        <p>Trusting the rhythm of your own unfolding. There is an intelligence at work in you that knows the way.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Invitation -->
  <section class="section section-cream">
    <div class="journey-content text-center">
      <h2>An Invitation</h2>
      <p>Every session I offer is an invitation to meet yourself where you are, with curiosity and tenderness, and to discover what becomes possible when you trust the intelligence of your own system.</p>
      <p>I'd love to have you and feel honoured to serve you — just where you are at this point in time.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Get in touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--color-meteorite-dark);
    color: var(--color-light);
    padding: 10rem 2rem 6rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-hero-inner {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    color: var(--color-light);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .page-hero p {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content-split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .content-text h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .content-text p {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--color-dark);
  }

  .content-image img {
    border-radius: 2px;
    box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(31, 19, 70, 0.1);
  }

  .journey-content {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .journey-content h2 {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .journey-content p {
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-dark);
  }

  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  .value-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-primary-light);
  }

  .value-card h3 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-meteorite);
  }

  .value-card p {
    color: var(--color-dark);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .content-split {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .values-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
